            "content": "# Ledger Architecture\n\n## High-Level Overview\n\nLedger is a C++ command-line double-entry accounting tool. Its architecture follows a clean\nthree-phase pipeline:\n\n```\nPlain-text journal files\n        |\n        v\n   [PARSING]          src/textual.cc (+ textual_directives.cc, textual_xacts.cc)\n        |              Reads directives, transactions, postings into journal_t\n        v\n   [PROCESSING]       src/filters.h/cc + src/chain.h/cc\n        |              Chain of Responsibility pipeline transforms/filters/aggregates postings\n        v\n   [REPORTING]        src/output.h/cc, src/print.h/cc, src/format.h/cc\n                       Terminal handlers render output via format strings\n```\n\n---\n\n## Scope Hierarchy (Three Tiers)\n\nLedger uses a three-tier scope hierarchy for option resolution and symbol lookup:\n\n```\nglobal_scope_t   (src/global.h)\n   |-- owns session_t\n   |-- owns ptr_list<report_t>  (stack; front = current)\n   |\nsession_t        (src/session.h)\n   |-- owns journal_t (shared_ptr)\n   |-- owns parse_context_stack_t\n   |\nreport_t         (src/report.h)\n       -- per-command option state\n       -- built-in expression functions\n       -- drives iterator + filter chain construction\n```\n\nExpression variable lookup walks the scope chain upward:\n`post_t → xact_t → item_t → session_t → global_scope_t`\n\n---\n\n## Entry Points\n\n### main() — src/main.cc\n\nThree execution modes, dispatched after argument parsing:\n\n1. **Batch mode** (default): `global_scope->execute_command_wrapper(args, false)`\n2. **Script mode** (`--script FILE`): iterate lines, call `execute_command_wrapper` per line\n3. **REPL mode** (no verb): read-eval-print loop using editline/readline\n\nStartup sequence:\n- `handle_debug_options()` — early scan for `--verify`, `--debug`, `--trace`, `--init-file`\n- Signal handlers (SIGINT, SIGPIPE)\n- `global_scope_t` construction — reads `LEDGER_*` env vars, parses init file\n- Argument parsing via `read_command_arguments()`\n\n### global_scope_t — src/global.h\n\n- `look_for_precommand()` — matches \"parse\", \"eval\", etc. (bypass journal loading)\n- `look_for_command()` — matches \"balance\", \"register\", \"print\", etc.\n- `execute_command()` — resolves verb → loads journal → opens output stream → invokes handler\n- `push_report()` / `pop_report()` — isolates per-command option state in REPL\n\n---\n\n## Core Data Model\n\n### journal_t — src/journal.h\n\nThe single root data structure for a session. Owns:\n- `account_t* master` — invisible root of the account tree (empty name, depth 0)\n- `account_t* bucket` — default account for elided amounts\n- `xacts_list xacts` — all regular transactions in parse order\n- `auto_xacts_list auto_xacts` — automated transactions (`= predicate`)\n- `period_xacts_list period_xacts` — periodic transactions (`~ period`) for budget/forecast\n- Mapping tables: `payee_alias_mappings`, `account_mappings`, `account_aliases`, etc.\n- `tag_check_exprs_map` — per-tag assertion expressions\n- `checking_style` — CHECK_PERMISSIVE / CHECK_NORMAL / CHECK_WARNING / CHECK_ERROR\n\nKey method: `add_xact()` — finalizes, auto-extends, validates metadata, deduplicates by UUID.\n\n### xact_t hierarchy — src/xact.h\n\nThree kinds of journal entries:\n- `xact_t` — regular dated transaction with payee and postings\n- `auto_xact_t` — automated transaction (`= /regex/`), applied by `journal_t::extend_xact()`\n- `period_xact_t` — periodic transaction (`~ monthly`) for budget/forecast generation\n\nAll inherit from `xact_base_t` → `item_t`.\n\n### post_t — src/post.h\n\nIndividual posting within a transaction:\n- `account_t* account` — target account\n- `amount_t amount` — the posted amount (with commodity)\n- `optional<expr_t> amount_expr` — deferred expression for computed amounts\n- `post_t::xdata_t` — ephemeral report-time state (running totals, display flags)\n- Flags: `POST_VIRTUAL`, `POST_MUST_BALANCE`, `POST_GENERATED`, etc.\n\n### account_t — src/account.h\n\nNode in the hierarchical chart of accounts:\n- `account_t* parent` — parent account (nullptr for master root)\n- `accounts_map accounts` — child accounts keyed by name segment\n- `account_t::xdata_t` — report-time aggregated totals\n\n### amount_t — src/amount.h\n\nPrecise arbitrary-precision monetary value using GMP/MPFR:\n- Internally stores a rational quantity + pointer to `commodity_t`\n- Supports infinite precision; precision expands on division/multiplication\n- Parse flags control behavior (PARSE_PARTIAL, PARSE_NO_MIGRATE, etc.)\n\n### value_t — src/value.h\n\nPolymorphic container for all expression engine results. Type hierarchy (least → most general):\n\n```\nVOID < BOOLEAN < DATETIME < DATE < INTEGER < AMOUNT < BALANCE\n     < STRING < MASK < SEQUENCE < SCOPE < ANY\n```\n\nUses reference-counted copy-on-write storage. A boolean test stays BOOLEAN; a running total\nstays INTEGER until a commoditized amount is added; only multi-commodity sums become BALANCE.\nThis avoids heap allocations for the common case.\n\n### balance_t — src/balance.h\n\nMap from `commodity_t*` to `amount_t`. Represents multi-commodity totals.\n\n### commodity_t / commodity_pool_t — src/commodity.h / src/pool.h\n\nGlobal pool of known commodities. Tracks price history (via `commodity_history_t` in\n`src/history.h`) for market-value calculations. Commodity annotations (lot price, date, tag)\nare held in `annotation_t` (src/annotate.h).\n\n---\n\n## Expression Engine\n\n### expr_t — src/expr.h\n\nThree-phase workflow for every expression string (e.g., `\"amount > 100\"`):\n\n1. **Parse** — `parser_t` (src/parser.h) converts text to an `op_t` AST\n2. **Compile** — resolve identifiers and fold constants against a `scope_t`\n3. **Evaluate (calc)** — walk the compiled AST per posting/account → `value_t`\n\n`merged_expr_t` extends `expr_t` for incremental composition: options like `-O`, `-B`, `-V`,\n`-A` each prepend/append transformations to a base expression.\n\nFast-path optimization: when an expression is a simple identifier like `\"amount\"`, callers\ncan bypass the full scope/calc machinery and read the posting field directly.\n\n### op_t — src/op.h\n\nThe AST node type. Represents operators (ADD, SUB, MUL, EQ, AND, OR…), identifiers, literals,\nfunction calls, etc. Evaluated by `op_t::calc()`.\n\n### scope_t — src/scope.h\n\nVirtual base for all scope levels. `lookup(kind, name)` returns an `expr_t::ptr_op_t` — a\npointer to the operator node that will evaluate the name. Each data type (post_t, xact_t,\naccount_t, session_t, global_scope_t) overrides `lookup()` to expose its own fields.\n\n`symbol_scope_t` extends `scope_t` to hold a named symbol table (for user-defined variables).\n`child_scope_t` holds a `parent` pointer for scope chain delegation.\n`bind_scope_t` binds a scope to an item for iteration.\n\n---\n\n## Filter Pipeline (Chain of Responsibility)\n\n### Base — src/chain.h\n\n```cpp\ntemplate <typename T>\nclass item_handler : public noncopyable {\n  std::shared_ptr<item_handler> handler;  // downstream handler\npublic:\n  virtual void operator()(T& item);  // process one item\n  virtual void flush();              // emit accumulated results\n  virtual void clear();              // reset for reuse\n};\n```\n\nTwo instantiations:\n- `post_handler_ptr = shared_ptr<item_handler<post_t>>`\n- `acct_handler_ptr = shared_ptr<item_handler<account_t>>`\n\n### Pipeline Construction — src/chain.cc\n\n`chain_handlers()` builds the full chain in inside-out order:\n\n```\nchain_post_handlers()   →  inner (downstream) portion\nchain_pre_post_handlers() →  outer (upstream) portion\n```\n\nSince each new handler wraps the previous, the **last added is outermost** (first to receive\npostings). Full flow for a register report (top = first to receive, bottom = output):\n\n```\n[posting source / iterator]\n  → budget_posts or forecast_posts      (conditional: --budget / --forecast)\n    → filter_posts(limit)               (re-applied if budget/forecast active)\n  → filter_posts(limit)                 (--limit)\n  → anonymize_posts                     (--anon)\n  → inject_posts                        (--inject)\n  → related_posts                       (--related)\n  → transfer_details(SET_PAYEE)         (--payee)\n  → transfer_details(SET_ACCOUNT)       (--account / --pivot)\n  → transfer_details(SET_DATE)          (--date)\n  → interval_posts                      (--period)\n  → day_of_week_posts / by_payee_posts  (--dow / --by-payee)\n  → posts_as_equity / subtotal_posts    (--equity / --subtotal)\n  → collapse_posts                      (--collapse / --depth)\n  → sort_posts / sort_xacts             (--sort / --sort-xacts)\n  → filter_posts(only)                  (--only)\n  → calc_posts                          (always: evaluates amount expr, running totals)\n  → changed_value_posts                 (--revalued / --unrealized)\n  → filter_posts(display)               (--display)\n  → display_filter_posts                (rounding adjustments)\n  → truncate_xacts                      (--head / --tail)\n  → [output handler: format_posts / format_accounts / print_xacts / ...]\n```\n\n### Key Filter Classes — src/filters.h\n\n| Class | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `calc_posts` | Core calculation: evaluates amount expr, computes running total |\n| `filter_posts` | Forward only if predicate matches (--limit, --display, --only) |\n| `interval_posts` | Group/subtotal by time period (--period) |\n| `subtotal_posts` | Combine into one entry per commodity/account |\n| `collapse_posts` | Collapse multi-posting xacts (--collapse) |\n| `sort_posts` | Accumulate then sort (--sort) |\n| `changed_value_posts` | Insert revaluation postings (--revalued) |\n| `budget_posts` | Generate budget postings from period_xacts |\n| `forecast_posts` | Generate forecast postings into future |\n| `transfer_details` | Rewrite date/account/payee from expression |\n| `post_splitter` | Group by expression value (--group-by) |\