            "content": "# Architecture\n\n## High-Level Data Flow\n\n```\nInput Files → Parsing → Journal → Filters Pipeline → Output Formatters → Report\n```\n\n1. **Parsing** (`textual.cc`, `textual_directives.cc`, `textual_xacts.cc`): Text journal files parsed into structured data\n2. **Journal** (`journal.h/cc`): Central container owning all accounts, transactions, directives\n3. **Processing** (`filters.h/cc`, `chain.h/cc`): Transactions flow through composable filter pipeline\n4. **Reporting** (`report.h/cc`, `output.h/cc`, `print.h/cc`, `format.h/cc`): Generate text reports\n\n## Core Abstractions\n\n| Class | File | Role |\n|-------|------|------|\n| `journal_t` | journal.h/cc | Top-level container: accounts, xacts, directives. One per session. |\n| `xact_t` | xact.h/cc | A dated transaction with metadata and postings |\n| `post_t` | post.h/cc | Line item within a transaction, links account to amount |\n| `account_t` | account.h/cc | Hierarchical chart of accounts (tree structure) |\n| `amount_t` | amount.h/cc | Precise arithmetic with commodity support (GMP/MPFR) |\n| `value_t` | value.h/cc | Polymorphic container: amounts, balances, strings, dates, sequences |\n| `expr_t` / `op_t` | expr.h/cc, op.h/cc | AST-based expression engine for queries and calculations |\n| `session_t` | session.h/cc | Manages journal lifecycle, commodity pool |\n| `report_t` | report.h/cc | Command dispatch, option handling, report generation |\n\n## Design Patterns\n\n- **Chain of Responsibility**: Filters (`filters.h/cc`) form a pipeline. Each filter receives posts, transforms/filters, and passes to the next. Built by `chain.cc`.\n- **Visitor Pattern**: Account tree traversal, transaction iteration\n- **AST Expressions**: `op_t` nodes form expression trees evaluated at runtime for queries, calculated amounts, format strings\n- **Value Semantics**: `amount_t`, `value_t` use value semantics with careful copy/move\n- **Template Flags**: `supports_flags<T>` template for type-safe bitfield flags on items/posts\n\n## Entry Points\n\n```\nmain.cc → global_t (global.h)\n  → session_t (session.h) — journal loading, commodity pool\n    → report_t (report.h) — command dispatch, options\n      → chain.cc — builds filter pipeline\n        → output.cc/print.cc — renders results\n```\n\n## Extension Points\n\n- **Python bindings** (`py_*.cc`, `pyinterp.cc`): Expose core types to Python via Boost.Python\n- **Expression language**: Custom functions, format strings, query predicates\n- **Automated transactions** (`xact.cc`): Rule-based transaction generation\n- **Periodic transactions**: Budget/forecast generation\n",
